main event: A farmer found two pieces of metal, approximately 4" x 5", painted green and yellow, on her farm.
interesting points: The farmer contacted the Air Force to get an opinion on the material.
The Air Force notified Randolph AFB, Strategic Air Command, to check the details.
The report mentions that the incident is part of the B-59 data.
The document appears to be a Project Blue Book record card.
The report does not contain any information about a sighted UFO object.
